rComments: mentions his cats or kids every lecture. the lectures are content-heavy he does not explain things well. The labs are confusing thankfully the TA just did it and gave everyone the answers. midterm 1 was very hard. try and pick a different prof if possible.

Overall, prof Steffener wasn't a terrible prof, as he cares about students and wants them to do well. But he makes learning the material very difficult with complicated explanations making it hard to know what to expect on the midterm and final. Although I did well in the course, many found it really difficult and hard.

I have a lot of mix emotions about this prof. He really made things difficult for us compared to the other sections I genuinely don't know if I'm the problem or not, but he tries to help out, but his midterm and final are difficult.

He really takes into account student feedback on his teaching and course content. Clearly cares about the subject matter and student success. Make sure to do all the readings, discussion posts, labs, etc because they will be used on the exams! Easy group project that was marked fair

Pretty good prof. He seems like he might not be the best but if you use the extra help he will answer all of your questions and do everything you ask him in order to help you succeed. I think he relies on feedback from students to see how he is teaching, so seriously ask for help and he will give it happily. Focus on lecture & labs, not textbook.

Make sure you do all the readings, activities, and videos he assigns for each week because his exams are very reflective of those! Midterm was a little difficult but the final was easier. Listen to his lectures on 2x speed (he talks slow) and attend his Q&A sessions because he provides a lot of helpful stuff! Passionate about what he teaches 4 sure

His teaching style is quite different than traditional profs. For each week there is a pre-recorded lecture, textbook chapter reading, assigned journal article reading, videos to watch, and mini online labs (not for grades but may see content on the exams). Caring guy, reach out if you have any concerns and he will listen. He wants you to do well!

It took a little bit of time to get used to his teaching style but for a first stats course I definitely recommend! He focuses on students understanding and applying the concepts of statistics. The quizzes, midterms and exam were extremely fair. I would very much recommend taking his class!
he really makes you work for your grade but overall fair. quizzes and exams were reflective of the material covered in the textbook.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lots of homework', 'Test heavy']

rComments: 2 other profs taught the class with him and he's hands down the best of the three. Tests and quizzes are mainly based on the articles and textbook, not the ppt. If you don't read them you're not gonna do well at all. Some qs r confusing and tricky but overall nice guy who just makes you work for your grade.

Worst prof I've EVER had. His tests are not at all reflective of what he teaches in lecture, he ignores student emails, refuses to alter his quizzes to reduce difficulty, and removes marks on term papers for changes made based on the recommendation of the TA. His online lectures are scattered and disorganized with his cats going crazy in the back.

Please do not take this prof. He makes the class seem so easy with his lectures but they do not reflect what he puts on his quizzes that are worth 45% of your mark or the midterm and exams. The textbook is your best friend but he words all the questions in a way so you will never be able to answer.

Does not respond to students in a timely manner. Quizzes and tests do not reflect course material at all. Questions are not comprehensive. No live lectures. No chance to ask questions. Almost every student did poorly on all aspects of testing.
How is this man still a prof? His lectures are all over the place, the quizzes were not reflective of the lecture material WHATSOEVER and he was not aware of several due dates/ class times etc.

Worst prof I've ever had, he can't teach at all. His quizzes are extremely difficult, almost totally unrelated to the lectures and expect a few of them every week. His instructions for his papers are also unclear.

Steffener doesn't teach. Simple as that - he provides us with docs, expects us to teach ourselves, assigns 2-3 quizzes a week (without indicating due dates or when a new one is up), and refuses to listen to student feedback on the difficulty of quizzes and content. Slides are extremely disorganized and the content covered is not reflected on tests

He just read everything from the textbook so if you miss a class, just make sure to read the chapter. His exams were extremely fair and grading was easy. Lots of little quizzes and exercises. He's hilarious but his videos are a bit dry as he is all over the place but overall a great prof.

If you talk to him in person and give specific examples of how your paper was unfairly graded, he will look at it (switched my 87 to a 97). Bases lectures and exams directly off of readings so its very easy to do well if you put the work in. He is funny and engaging and very fair. He breaks down concepts meticulously and is very prompt with emails.

Basically left everything up to the TAs in terms of the paper - he completely ignored our emails. TAs were extremely unfair in marking it. His lectures are good, and heavily based on his assigned readings. Final was based on slides and lectures. He's a nice guy, I just wish he cared about his students doing well on the paper assignment...
Decent and fair prof.

This is my second time taking a class with Jason Steffener. His readings are crucial; you have to do it. His exams are mostly from his lectures and slides, which are based on the readings. Very Ethical and Fair professor
teacherRatingTags: ['Group projects', 'Get ready to read', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Fair evaluations and rubrics, open to feedback and regrading when necessary. Really interesting and clear lectures. Overall just an excellent prof. He goes over exam Qs and takes off the ones that students don't do well on. Do the readings, go to classes, and review your lectures. Exams are totally from the lectures (which are based off readings)

Fav HSS prof ever! Had him for 2 classes now and I highly recommend! Lectures are straight from readings so do them and go to class and you'll do well. Interesting lectures, PPs are well organized around the readings. Gives clear expectations for papers and fair rubrics. Answers emails efficiently, happy to answer Qs after class. Overall just great

My favourite prof of all time. He is passionate and knows how to make the material interesting, you feel like you're researching with him while he teaches. I've taken 2 classes with him so far and plan on taking another one next semester because I always look forward to his lectures!

His evaluations are very picky- he chooses to focus on minuscule details rather than ability to engage with and expand on the big picture. Relies way too much on multiple choice for a class that should be about critical thinking and understanding. Lectures are slow and unnecessary but he gives hints on what random details to mindlessly memorize

Straight A keener but I hated his class and evals. Lecture material was usually interesting but the lectures themselves were slow, repetitive, oversimplified and heavy with useless class discussions that you could never hear anyways. Exams were made hard with names/nitpicky dates/terms. No room for critical engagement & he's resistant to feedback

Steffener is a decent prof - he teaches with a lot of examples, but this course was pretty simple material and he covered it effectively. He tells us what to know for exams and best of all he tells us what to focus on for readings. Nice guy, relatively easy course. Definitely a solid choice.

Avoid if you can. He has alot of knowledge about what he is teaching but he doesnt know how to get it across to students. He reads off his slides and doesnt know how to explain the material so he just gives examples. LOTS of readings where he highlights stuff he wants you to know, not sure how that applies to the exams bc the MCQs are so random
Cool guy. New to teaching but very good. You can tell he likes his position and what he teaches about. Univ of Ottowa is lucky to have him!!
Dr. Steffener is just the best!!! He is a neat person and very inspiring. He is very responsive and always helps you out whenever you need.

Dr. Steffener was a great prof to have!   Being a fairly new prof you can tell he is very motivated to make his lectures interesting for the students. He had guests come in to talk about their research related to the course topic  Grading criteria: 4 quizzes (12.5% x 4), 1 paper (25% individual), 1 presentation (25% partners)  9/10 would recommend
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: He organized the course into 4 units, so you could forget everything about each unit once you wrote the quiz. 4 quizzes total, and you pick which topic to write your term paper on + which one to do a presentation on. Presentations in groups but you're marked individually :). His lectures are a little dry, but the course is an easy A. Recommend!

The course was pretty interesting, the prof had a clear grading criteria 4 quizzes, one paper and one presentation. no final exam and no textbook. Jason take student feedback and he is always improving! don't take the selected topic course with any other prof
Steffener put in the effort with this course and made an effort for everyone to understand. The course appeared easy but then the final exam and final project were brutal and no one did well.

Not a good prof. Midterm was okay (all out of textbook). Tough grader when it comes to marking papers (sent out an email saying too many people are bugging him about an unhappy mark). Final was unfair as it had random stat problems that he doesn't properly teach in class. Also, his MCQs are worth 2 marks each, so your mark may end up being lower.

Really nice guy, but he's a new prof and doesn't have a lot of teaching experience. He means well but the course content isn't always conveyed very effectively. That said, he's very helpful if you're struggling. Plus, it's relatively easy to do well.  He marked the paper (group project) generously, which is always nice.

He made this class pretty easy. His lectures can be all over the place but her try his best to make it simple for the students. The paper had a nice concept but find you a good group! Midterm and final were pretty much based on the book!

Really great prof who takes the time to ensure that students understand what the material is all about. Super helpful when students have questions outside of class for office hours and he takes students suggestions about the course and ideas and actually alters lectures etc from it.  Fair midterms and final.  A if you put in the regular HSS effort

1st time being a prof. Engineer. Means well but doesn't convey material effectively. Midterm OK but the final was extremely difficult: heavily weighted on stats (which we had 2 informal lectures on with no chapter in the textbook nor lecture slides to study from) and quant methods (1 lecture). Didn't mark our research papers before final exam. :-(

Terrible professor. He has good intentions but mumbles to himself the whole time he lectures and is not effective at conveying course material. Midterm was fair but exam was impossible and did not reflect course content at all. Heads up - he also never replies to emails and if he does it's like a week later
What a great professor ! Truly enjoyed taking this course with him.
